<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Jude Bellingham scored on his competitive debut as Borussia Dortmund started the season with a comfortable 5-0 victory over MSV Duisburg in the DFB-Pokal first round.</p>

<p>Fellow Englishman Jadon Sancho put Dortmund ahead from the spot after 14 minutes against the German third division side before Bellingham became Dortmund's youngest ever scorer with a tidy finish. </p>

<p>The hosts were reduced to ten men on 38 minutes as Dominic Volkmer was sent his marching orders and their misery was compounded when Thorgan Hazard netted from the resulting free-kick. Giovanni Reyna and Marco Reus added to the scoreline in the second half.</p>

<p>Jude Bellingham scored on his competitive debut as Borussia Dortmund beat MSV Duisburg</p>

<p>Jadon Sancho put the Bundesliga side ahead after 14 minutes from the penalty spot</p>

<p>The 17-year-old doubled Dortmund's lead with a tidy finish to become their youngest scorer</p>

<p>Thorgan Hazard scored a sumptuous free-kick as Dortmund went 3-0 up before half time</p>

<p>Giovanni Reyna carried on Dortmund's dominance after the break to put them 4-0 up</p>

<p>Marco Reus scored his side's fifth after coming on as a second half substitute</p>
